I"ˇH<p>This is a list of the books I read in 2022.<label for="read" class="margin-toggle sidenote-number"></label><input type="checkbox" id="read" class="margin-toggle" /><span class="sidenote">I didn‚Äôt read every word in every one of these books, but I‚Äôm not including books I gave up on, or books I just picked a chapter out of. There are a few textbooks on here ‚Äî only included if I read them through, tho with no requirements for completing the exercises. I feel like I‚Äôve earned the right to include Mas-Collel, but will respect the integrity of the list.  </span>  ‚òÖ means I loved it; 15 books earned a ‚òÖ. I re-read about 20 books from previous years; these are marked with a ‚ü≥. Some books were re-reads within the year, too ‚Äî I read Jeff Smith‚Äôs <strong>Bone</strong> twice; most of <strong>The Oxford Book of Essays</strong> twice, and <strong>Hamlet</strong> four times. 30 of these books, about a quarter, were translated from another language.</p>

<p>The books are in reverse order of when I put them into Zotero; I read some books right away, while others waited around for four or ten months until the time was right. I read all but three of these books on my tablet.</p>

